Coordinating Meeting of International Council for Settlement of Japan's Past Crimes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- A coordinating meeting of the International Council for Solidarity with the Struggle for the Settlement of Japan's Past Crimes was held in Taipei of China on Jan. 20 and 21.
 Present there were delegates and personages from various countries and regions demanding Japan's settlement of its past including the DPRK, China, the Netherlands, the Philippines, the United States and Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting heard the information about the activities of organizations and personages of various countries and regions after the fourth meeting of the council held in Manila in August last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting bitterly denounced the Japanese reactionaries for craftily attempting to evade the state responsibility for the issue of the "comfort women" drafted for the imperial Japanese army and hush up the issue of the remains of victims of forcible drafting of Koreans, while upgrading the Defence Agency to a ministry and becoming all the more outspoken in their maneuvers to step up the retrogressive revision of the constitution and the fundamental law of education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting discussed and decided upon concrete measures and ways for invigorating international solidarity activities. It called for intensifying activities urging parliaments of different countries to adopt resolutions and others demanding a settlement to the issue related to the "comfort women" and building global public opinion sharply denouncing through the UN human rights organizations the Japanese authorities' inhumane act of leaving uncared the remains of victims of forcible drafting of Koreans though more than 60 years have passed since the defeat of Japan in the war and demanding its early solution. It also called for undertaking activities to condemn and reject the ever more blatant moves of the Japanese reactionaries to distort history and militarize the country and thwart the attempt of Japan to get UNSC permanent membership while avoiding apology and compensation for its past crimes.

GNP Denounced for Inciting National Confrontation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly held a meeting on Jan. 24 to denounce the "Grand National Party" for fanning up national confrontation.
 The resolution read out at the meeting recalled that the GNP on Jan. 19 put pressure on the "government" to stop inter-Korean cooperation and exchange, crying that "the lifting of sanctions against the north must not be discussed at the six-party talks".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crisis of war on the Korean Peninsula has heightened because the United States ran riot in its hostile policy toward the DPRK and planning of a preemptive nuclear attack on it in violation of the agreement with it, the resolution said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This being a hard reality, the GNP is inciting national confrontation, parroting the U.S. claim that the north should give up its nuclear program first. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It demanded a prompt dissolution of the GNP which is whipping up national confrontation, not caring a dime for the outbreak of a war on this land owing to the U.S. moves for a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula.

Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works Vol. 67 Off Press 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works Vol. 67 was brought out by the Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House. It is the library of the immortal Juche idea which carries his famous works systematically and comprehensively on a chronological order.
 Contained in the book are 31 famous works such as historic speeches, concluding addresses and talks made by President Kim Il Sung from May to August, Juche 67 (1978). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It deals with the original ideas, theories and policies set forth by him for the revolutionary struggle of the Korean people to effect a great upswing in socialist construction and the victory of the cause of global independence with his extraordinary intelligence and outstanding foresight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "On Our Country's Experience in the Solution of the Rural Question", "The International Friendship Exhibition Is Precious Historic Wealth to Be Handed Down to Posterity", "On Greeting the 30th Anniversary of the Republic with High Degree of Political Enthusiasm and Brilliant Achievements in Labor" and other works indicate policies for effecting a new great upswing in all fields and units of the national economy and improving the standard of people's living and ways for their implementation and questions of principle in strengthening education in revolutionary tradition and education in socialist patriotism among the members of the WPK and other working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "The General Association of Korean Residents in Japan Should Conduct Well the External Work to Actively Contribute to the Cause of National Reunification" and other works elucidate strategic and tactical matters in accelerating the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, the book indicates the matter of our experience in socialist construction, questions of principle for strengthening the unity and solidarity of the Non-aligned Movement and other questions arising in triumphantly advancing the world revolution.

No Force on Earth Can Ever Stop Koreans' Dynamic Advance for Independent Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- No force on earth can ever stop the dynamic advance of the Korean nation for independent reunification full of conviction of sure victory and optimism, Rodong Sinmun Monday says in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The movement of Koreans for reunification is undergoing throes and ups and downs due to the separatists at home and abroad. But it is an inexorable law of historical development that the historic cause of achieving national independence is sure to be crowned with a final victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an inevitable trend of the national history and a legitimate requirement for national development that the Korean nation who had been divided into two by the outsiders is sure to become one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the defeat of the Japanese imperialists the U.S. imperialists occupied south Korea and have since imposed upon the Koreans the tragedy resulting from national division and infringed upon their sovereignty. However, this can never quell the desire and will of the Koreans to put an end to the history of division and achieve national reunification and thus realize independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification had to undergo hardships and trials due to the desperate efforts of the outsiders and anti-reunification forces. But it has been preserved and advanced along the orbit of independent reunification thanks to the strong desire of all the Koreans and their staunch struggle for reunification. "By our nation itself", the idea guiding the era, has served as a banner guiding the national movement for independent reunification despite difficulties and hardships. All the Koreans are waging a dynamic movement for independent reunification, while frustrating the moves of the outsiders and sycophantic and treacherous forces for a war and their anti-reunification campaign. This reality goes to prove that the history of the Korean nation is making dynamic progress toward independent reunification despite blatant challenge and test of history.

Reckless Remarks of Commander of U.S. Forces in S. Korea under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the commander of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops in south Korea stressed the need to keep the "UN Command" even in peacetime to cope with the wartime, asserting that the role of the "UN Commander" should not be weakened even after the disbandment of the U.S.-south Korea "combined forces command" in the wake of the transfer of the "right to control wartime operation." 
 In this regard, Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary terms his outcry reckless remarks betraying the U.S. bellicose forces' design to perpetuate the U.S. forces' presence in south Korea and invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are asserting that it is necessary to keep the "UN Command" even after the disbandment of the U.S.-south Korea "combined forces command," talking about the "vacuum in the military command system." This is prompted by their sinister intention to perpetuate the presence of their forces in south Korea and invade the DPRK and, furthermore, continue abusing the name of UN for the purpose of maintaining their military hegemony in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' plan to transfer the "right to control wartime operation" to the south Korean army and disband the "combined forces command" does not mean that they are ready to terminate the U.S. forces' presence in south Korea and give up the right to command and control the south Korean army and their moves for a war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is clearly evidenced by the remarks made by the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea about the necessity to keep the "UN Command." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts patently prove that the U.S. bellicose forces are chiefly to blame for wrecking peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula and bringing the dark clouds of a nuclear war to hang over it.

U.S. Imperialists' Preparations for Biological and Chemical War Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The United States is a ferocious aggressor who does not hesitate to use very homicidal weapons of mass destruction (WMD) to meet its aggressive interests and an inhuman criminal state posing a grave threat to the existence and security of humankind. Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary.
 Citing the crime-woven history of the U.S. imperialists in which they have used Koreans as targets of their biological and chemical warfare since the period of the past Korean war in a bid to carry out their policy of domination over Korea, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists started the horrible biological and chemical warfare against the Korean people on Jan. 28, 1952 on a full scale to recover from their setbacks in the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From that day to March 25 of the same year, the U.S. imperialists dropped different types of germ bombs containing bacteria of cholera, typhus and pest in more than 400 areas in the northern half of Korea over 700 times. In the subsequent period, too, they used toxic gas bombs and poisonous chemical weapons, massacring Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They shipped defoliant into south Korea in the 1960s and then built at least 10 toxic gas factories to mass-produce various types of chemical weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. scenario for biological and chemical warfare became evermore undisguised after the appearance of the Bush administration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is said that a large laboratory covering an area of 27,000 square feet is now under construction in Maryland which is expected to kick off experiments for germ warfare by use of such malignant germs as bacillus anthraces and Yesinia pestis from late this year or from the next year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is by no means fortuitous that the U.S. has always included chemical warfare exercises in all the large-scale war exercises including "Ulji Focus Lens" military exercise in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is the increasing danger of the outbreak of the second Korean war to be accompanied by biochemical warfare on the Korean Peninsula due to the U.S. imperialists' war moves. This cannot but be a grave menace to the very existence and security of the Korean people and the rest of humankind.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 4th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's famous work "Songun-Based Revolutionary Line Is a Great Revolutionary Line of Our Era and an Ever-Victorious Banner of Our Revolution".
 The work, published on Jan. 29, Juche 92 (2003), clarifies the theoretical and practical issues arising in enforcing the Songun politics including the essence and nature of the Songun politics, its starting point and scientific theoretical analysis of the circumstances of the present times, a new view and viewpoint on the issue related to the main force of the revolution and on the role of the revolutionary army, the reason why the People's Army was put forward as the main force of the Korean revolution and the factor that prompted the People's Army to creditably perform such mission and duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed article says: The validity and vitality of the Songun revolutionary line laid down by Kim Jong Il have been fully proved in the practice of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The powerful war deterrent built under the banner of Songun has provided a sure guarantee for protecting the sovereignty and dignity of the nation and preserving peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons and people of the DPRK are immensely proud of having the tremendous war deterrent capable of firmly defending the sovereignty and dignity of the nation and ensuring durable peace in this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity of the DPRK, the first of its kind in the world, has grown stronger than ever before under the banner of Songun. A dynamic drive has been waged to learn from the ideological and moral world and fighting traits of the People's Army replete with the spirit of devotedly protecting the headquarters of the revolution. It is against this background that the single-minded unity in the era of Songun has grown to be the unity and cohesion of the whole Party and army and all the people based on the monolithic ideology and faith and comradely love and sense of obligation, signifying a new height in the unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great leaping advance made in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation on the basis of the revolutionary soldier spirit represents a shining success achieved in the efforts to implement the Songun revolutionary line of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The servicepersons and people have ushered in a new glorious era of creation and changes by working miracles of the history in the revolutionary soldier spirit holding aloft the banner of Songun under the leadership of the great Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics, Songun revolutionary line of the Party, serves as a great revolutionary line of our era and an all-powerful treasured sword as it has always brought victory and a new era of creation and changes to this land.

Information and Motivational Activities Brisk in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- A brisk motivational campaign for inspiring the entire people to implementing the tasks set forth by the joint New Year editorial has been undertaken in the DPRK.
 The Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House, the Mansudae Art Studio and the Central Fine Arts Studio have created many posters calling upon the Korean people to effect innovations in their advance for the year. Among them are posters "Beat louder the drum of Songun revolution!", "Forward to high eminence of great, prosperous powerful socialist nation!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The newspapers come out every day with editorials, articles and items calling for carrying out the tasks put forth by the joint editorial, and TV and radios broadcast revolutionary and militant songs and music. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Pyongyang City Art Propaganda Troupe conduct radio and oral motivational activities at the Pyongyang Thermal Power Complex and East Pyongyang Thermal-power Plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of the South Hamgyong Provincial Art Propaganda Troupe went to various co-op farms, carrying with them a large amount of manure and farm implements, and encouraged peasants in their farming preparation with radio scripts and story-telling pieces to bring the tasks of the joint editorial home to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The South Phyongan, Kangwon and Jagang Provincial art propaganda troupes are giving traveling performances and conducting agitation activities at industrial establishments and coal mines in their provinces, in congratulation of the signal successes made by workers from the beginning of the year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such vigorous songs as "Forward, Everybody on General March of Songun Revolution", "Are We Living Like in Those Days?" and "We Will Advance with Confidence" bring to fuller play the revolutionary zeal of the working people.

Thaechon Youth Power Station No. 4
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The Thaechon Youth Power Station No. 4 has been built in Thaechon, North Phyongan Province of the DPRK, one more edifice of the era of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Its construction was initiated in accordance with the far-reaching plan of President Kim Il Sung for erecting large hydro-power stations in the Thaechon area by the Juche-oriented unique method of developing water-power resources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True to the behests of the President, the people of North Phyongan Province successfully carried out the gigantic project in a few years with their own efforts and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the final stage of the dam project, the dam was exposed to danger owing to the long-spell of rain. Then, the youth shock brigade members and working people of Nyongbyon County devotedly saved the dam from the torrential water by carrying earth-packed bags on their back, thus making a decisive breakthrough in the construction of the power station. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The builders, with this spirit, excavated earth for the foundations of the generating room and the sluiceway in the biting cold water in the depth of the winter and ran some 40 kilometers a day to carry gravels, sand and concrete mixture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Workers of the machine-building plants in Rakwon, Kusong and other areas of the province manufactured facilities needed for the power station in time under manifold difficulties, thus contributing to completing the construction ahead of the set-time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dam built across the broad Taeryong River, the large artificial lake, generating room and power distribution room are the fruition of the devoted efforts bent by the constructors to build the power station as a grand monumental edifice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those days, "The River Taeryong Tells", the collection of works written by them has seen the light. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent completion following to the Thaechon Youth Power Stations Nos. 1, 2, 3 and 5 makes it possible to effectively use the water resources abundant in the north-western area of the country in producing electricity and supplying ample irrigation water to the west coast area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While looking round the Thaechon Youth Power Station No. 4 some time ago, Kim Jong Il highly appreciated the heroic feats performed by the constructors in building the great edifice which would shine long in history, saying that it was the spirit and mettle of Thaechon.

Protest Voiced against Japanese Reactionaries' Moves against DPRK and Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The National Executive Committee of the Polish Communist Party and the Finland-Korea Society on Jan. 21 and 22 sent letters to the Japanese embassies in their countries in protest against the Japanese reactionaries' hostile policy toward the DPRK and their suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 The National Executive Committee of the Polish Communist Party in its letter said the persecution and repression committed in the form of search of organs under Chongryon and houses of its officials and blocking of trips and contacts are obviously an encroachment upon the rights of the Koreans in Japan and a blatant violation of international law and the UN Charter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter of the Finland-Korea Society warned that the suppression of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan by the Japanese authorities would result in further aggravating the DPRK-Japan relations, inciting the anti-Japanese sentiments of the Korean people and destabilizing the regional situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing concern over the act of the Japanese authorities trying to take issue even with goods of the category of humanitarian cooperation, the letters demanded a prompt stop to it.
